§ Main result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The orthogonal complement of a subspace is a subspace. ⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $L ⊂ 𝗥^n$ be a subspace. Then
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \dim L + \dim L^{⊥} = n. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $b_1, …, b_m$ be a basis for a subspace $L ⊂ 𝗥^n$.
    Then $x ⟂L$ if and only if $x ⟂b_i$ for $i = \upto{m}$. ⦉
</statement>
